5 the use of the Internet website or online portal; and
6 (b) The amount of any fee charged to the tenant by the
7 landlord or his or her agent for the use of the Internet website or
8 online portal must be separately identified in any written rental
9 agreement.
10 Sec. 3. 1. A tenant who is aggrieved by a violation of
11 subsection 6 or 7 of NRS 118A.200 may bring a civil action in any
12 court of competent jurisdiction for such a violation.
13 2. If a tenant prevails in an action brought pursuant to
14 subsection 1, the court shall award the tenant:
15 (a) Any damages the tenant has sustained that the court deems
16 appropriate;
17 (b) Any equitable relief that the court deems appropriate;
18 (c) The tenant’s costs in the action and reasonable attorney’s
19 fees; and
20 (d) Statutory damages of $250 for each violation which
21 involved deception.
22 Sec. 4. A landlord or his or her agent shall, upon request,
23 provide to a prospective tenant a copy of the written rental
24 agreement, if any, to which the prospective tenant would be
25 subject if he or she were to become a tenant.
26 Sec. 4.5. 1. A landlord who collects from a prospective
27 tenant any fee to apply to rent a dwelling unit, including, without
28 limitation, an application fee, a fee to obtain a credit report or a
29 fee to obtain a background check, shall refund the fee to the
30 prospective tenant if the landlord:
31 (a) Rents the dwelling unit to a different prospective tenant;
32 and
33 (b) Does not conduct the activity for which the fee was
34 collected, including, without limitation, processing the application
35 or obtaining a credit report or background check of the
36 prospective tenant.
37 2. A landlord shall not collect an application fee, a fee to
38 obtain a credit report or a fee to obtain a background check for a
39 minor who is a member of the household of the prospective tenant.
40 3. As used in this section:
41 (a) “Household” means an association of persons who live in
42 the same home or dwelling and who are related by blood,
43 adoption, marriage or domestic partnership.
44 (b) “Minor” means a person who is under 18 years of age.
